```

### 3. Define Avro Schemas

Define your event schemas in Avro format and register them with the schema registry.

#### Example Avro Schema for `OrderCreatedEvent`:

```json
{
  "namespace": "com.example.ordermanagement",
  "type": "record",
  "name": "OrderCreatedEvent",
  "fields": [
    { "name": "orderId", "type": "string" },
    { "name": "createdAt", "type": "long" } // Unix timestamp
  ]
}
```

Register this schema with the Schema Registry:

```sh
curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/vnd.schemaregistry.v1+json" \
     --data '{"schema": "{\"namespace\": \"com.example.ordermanagement\",\"type\": \"record\",\"name\": \"OrderCreatedEvent\",\"fields\": [{\"name\": \"orderId\", \"type\": \"string\"}, {\"name\": \"createdAt\", \"type\": \"long\"}]}"}' \
     http://localhost:8081/subjects/order-created-value/versions
```

