Exactly-Once Semantics (EOS) in Apache Kafka ensures that each message is processed exactly once, even in the presence of failures or retries. This is crucial for maintaining data integrity and consistency in distributed systems. Here’s a step-by-step guide on how to set up EOS end-to-end with producers and consumers.

### 1. Producer Configuration

To enable Exactly-Once Semantics (EOS) at the producer level, you need to configure your Kafka producers to use idempotent and transactional modes.

