By following the above steps, you can set up a robust Saga pattern in your distributed order management system. This setup ensures that each step of an operation is completed successfully before proceeding to the next one and rolls back any partially completed transactions if an error occurs. Additionally, it leverages transactional producers and consumers for exactly-once semantics (EOS) and includes proper error handling and retry mechanisms.

This approach provides a solid foundation for managing complex workflows in your distributed system while ensuring data integrity and consistency even in the presence of failures or restarts.
