When integrating retries with Dead-Letter Queues (DLQ), it's important to ensure that messages that fail repeatedly due to transient issues can be moved to a DLQ for further analysis and potential reprocessing. Here’s how you can configure your system to handle retries in conjunction with DLQs:

### 1. Retry Logic Configuration

Implement retry logic within your consumers to attempt processing failed messages multiple times before moving them to the DLQ.

#### Example Retry Logic:
```java
import org.springframework.retry.annotation.Backoff;
import org.springframework.retry.annotation.Retryable;

@Component
public class InventoryConsumer {

    @Autowired
    private KafkaTemplate<String, GenericRecord> kafkaTemplate;

    @Retryable(value = Exception.class, maxAttempts = 3, backoff = @Backoff(delay = 1000))
    public void processOrderCreated(ConsumerRecord<String, GenericRecord> record) {
        try {
            // Process the event and commit offset manually if needed
            inventoryService.adjustInventory(record.value());
            consumer.commitSync(Collections.singletonMap(new TopicPartition(record.topic(), record.partition()), new OffsetAndMetadata(record.offset() + 1)));
        } catch (Exception e) {
            logger.error("Failed to process order created event: " + record.toString(), e);
            // Retry logic or dead letter queue handling
        }
    }

    private void sendToDLQ(ConsumerRecord<String, GenericRecord> record) {
        kafkaTemplate.send("order-created-dlq", record.key(), record.value());
    }
}
```

### 2. Dead-Letter Queue Handling

When a message fails after the maximum number of retries, move it to the DLQ for further analysis or reprocessing.

#### Example DLQ Configuration:
```java
import org.apache.kafka.clients.consumer.ConsumerRecord;
import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;
import org.springframework.kafka.annotation.KafkaListener;

@Component
public class InventoryConsumer {

    @Autowired
    private KafkaTemplate<String, GenericRecord> kafkaTemplate;

    @KafkaListener(topics = "order-created", groupId = "inventory-group")
    public void listenOrderCreated(ConsumerRecord<String, GenericRecord> record) {
        try {
            // Process the event and commit offset manually if needed
            inventoryService.adjustInventory(record.value());
            consumer.commitSync(Collections.singletonMap(new TopicPartition(record.topic(), record.partition()), new OffsetAndMetadata(record.offset() + 1)));
        } catch (Exception e) {
            logger.error("Failed to process order created event: " + record.toString(), e);
            // Retry logic or dead letter queue handling
            if (!retryTemplate.execute(context -> {
                try {
                    inventoryService.adjustInventory(record.value());
                    consumer.commitSync(Collections.singletonMap(new TopicPartition(record.topic(), record.partition()), new OffsetAndMetadata(record.offset() + 1)));
                    return null;
                } catch (Exception ex) {
                    logger.error("Failed to process order created event after retry: " + record.toString(), ex);
                    sendToDLQ(record);
                    throw ex; // Rethrow exception to trigger next retry
                }
            })) {
                logger.warn("Max retries reached for message, moving to DLQ");
                sendToDLQ(record);
            }
        }
    }

    private void sendToDLQ(ConsumerRecord<String, GenericRecord> record) {
        kafkaTemplate.send("order-created-dlq", record.key(), record.value());
    }
}
```

